casebody.data:
Melissa SIARS, Appellant,
v.
Sandra DANSBY and Division of Employment Security, Respondents. No. ED 106557 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION ONE. Filed: December 18, 2018
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied January 23, 2019 FOR APPELLANT: Melissa Siars, Appellant Acting Pro Se. FOR RESPONDENT: Sandra Dansby, Respondent Acting Pro Se, Meaghan M. Forck, Atty. for Division of Employment Security, 421 East Dunklin Street, Jefferson City, MO 65101, Bruce Farmer, Co-Counsel for Division of Employment Security, 33175 West Truman Blvd., Jefferson City, MO 65102. Before Roy L. Richter, P.J., Robert M. Clayton III, J., and Angela T. Quigless, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM.

Melissa Siars appeals the decision of the Labor and Industrial Relations Commission ("the Commission") denying her unemployment benefits. We find no error has occurred.

No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. We have, however, provided the parties a memorandum setting forth the reasons for our decision. The decision of the Commission is affirmed under Rule 84.16(b).
